Quote from $2million book - the real risk takers

This is how I built my account - winners like CMG, EOG... propelled my account to the level of confidence that I needed for day trading. But then I continued that mentality of long term investing in my swing trading, and for some reason... buying the dips didn't work in 2014.

&nbsp;

Long term investing - when it makes sense depends on the age of the bull market

&nbsp;

Ultimate trap to bag holding and huge unrealized losses.  Being a prudent trader is about being liquid. Defending your account so the capital is there when you need it.

